"""
1. What happens if JSON has multiple data?

If the JSON is flat (keyâ€“value pairs), Pandas can directly convert it into a DataFrame.

If the JSON is nested or has multiple records, Pandas needs you to tell it how to handle the structure.


"""
json file 
==========
[
  {"Name": "Alice", "Age": 25, "Salary": 50000},
  {"Name": "Bob", "Age": 30, "Salary": 60000},
  {"Name": "Charlie", "Age": 35, "Salary": 70000}
]

python code 
===========
import pandas as pd

df = pd.read_json("employees.json")
print(df)

======================
But
======
#When JSON is nested
{
  "employees": [
    {"Name": "Alice", "Details": {"Age": 25, "Salary": 50000}},
    {"Name": "Bob", "Details": {"Age": 30, "Salary": 60000}}
  ]
}

import pandas as pd
import json

# Load JSON
with open("nested.json") as f:
    data = json.load(f)

# Flatten
df = pd.json_normalize(data["employees"])
print(df)
